The paper investigates the connections between decision forests and convolutional neural networks for image classification, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the trade-off between accuracy and efficiency, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new family of hybrid models, which involves data transformation and explicit data routing functions, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of sparse weight matrices, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed models on image classification tasks, which is a common application in natural language processing (cs.CL).
